---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | BrixiaTech"
  description="Information on the processing of personal data of users of brixiatech.com, pursuant to Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR)."
  hrefIt="/privacy/"
  hrefEn="/en/privacy/"
>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="legal__inner">
      <h1 class="legal__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: 3 July 2026</p>

      <p class="legal__lead">
        Pursuant to Articles 13 and 14 of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (&ldquo;GDPR&rdquo;) and Italian
        Legislative Decree 196/2003 as amended by Legislative Decree 101/2018 (the &ldquo;Privacy
        Code&rdquo;), this notice describes how the personal data of users who visit the website
        <strong>brixiatech.com</strong> and who contact the company are processed.
      </p>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
        <p>
          The Data Controller is <strong>SAL-FER Srl</strong> (of which BrixiaTech is a commercial
          brand), in the person of its legal representative pro tempore, <strong>Roberto Goffi</strong>:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Registered office: Via G. Di Vittorio 15, 25037 Pontoglio (BS), Italy</li>
          <li>Operational office: Via F.lli Calvi 19, Palazzolo sull&rsquo;Oglio (BS), Italy &mdash; San Pancrazio</li>
          <li>VAT no. 03726890985 &mdash; Brescia Companies Register, REA BS-558109</li>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:info@brixiatech.com">info@brixiatech.com</a></li>
          <li>Certified email (PEC): <a href="mailto:salfersrl@gigapec.it">salfersrl@gigapec.it</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          No Data Protection Officer (DPO) has been appointed, as the conditions set out in Article
          37 GDPR do not apply. For any matter relating to the processing of your data and to
          exercise your rights, you may write to the contacts above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>2. Types of data processed</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>a) Browsing data.</strong> In the course of their normal operation, the IT systems
          and software procedures responsible for running the website acquire certain data whose
          transmission is implicit in the use of Internet communication protocols (for example IP
          addresses, browser type, request times, technical security data). This data is processed
          automatically by the infrastructure that delivers the website and is not used to identify
          users.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>b) Data voluntarily provided by the user.</strong> The website contains no
          data-collection forms. Contact takes place through the channels indicated (email,
          telephone, WhatsApp). When a user chooses to contact the company, they provide the data
          contained in the communication: typically name, email address or telephone number, and the
          content of the message, including any project details.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>c) Cookies.</strong> The website uses only necessary technical cookies (see
          Section 4).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>3. Purposes and legal bases of processing</h2>
        <div class="legal__row">
          <p class="legal__row-purpose">Responding to contact and quotation requests</p>
          <p class="legal__row-basis">Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR &mdash; performance of pre-contractual measures taken at the data subject&rsquo;s request.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal__row">
          <p class="legal__row-purpose">Providing, operating and securing the website (technical logs)</p>
          <p class="legal__row-basis">Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR &mdash; the Controller&rsquo;s legitimate interest in the continuity and security of the service.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="legal__row">
          <p class="legal__row-purpose">Compliance with legal obligations (tax, accounting) where a contractual relationship arises</p>
          <p class="legal__row-basis">Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR &mdash; legal obligation.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          The website uses only <strong>necessary technical cookies</strong>, for which consent is
          not required under Article 122 of the Privacy Code. There are no profiling, analytics or
          third-party advertising cookies; for this reason no consent banner is present.
        </p>
        <p>
          The technical cookies used relate to the security and content-delivery infrastructure
          (Cloudflare), for example:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>__cf_bm</code> &mdash; anti-bot protection; expires after 30 minutes of continuous user inactivity (duration per official Cloudflare documentation; not configurable).</li>
          <li><code>cf_clearance</code> &mdash; set only after a security check (challenge) has been passed; default duration 30 minutes, configurable by the Controller via Challenge Passage (duration per official Cloudflare documentation).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>5. Recipients of data and data processors</h2>
        <p>
          Data may be processed, on behalf of the Controller, by the following parties acting as data
          processors (Art. 28 GDPR) or as independent controllers, each for their own technical
          purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> &mdash; website hosting, content delivery (CDN) and security services; processes browsing data and IP addresses. Based in the USA.</li>
          <li><strong>Hostinger International Ltd</strong> &mdash; email hosting; processes the data contained in received emails as data processor (Art. 28 GDPR). EU-based company, subject to the GDPR; email data resides on a server located in the Netherlands (EU), with backups in Lithuania (EU): no extra-EU transfer.</li>
          <li><strong>Meta Platforms</strong> (WhatsApp service) &mdash; only where the user chooses to contact the company via WhatsApp; processes the number and the content of the conversation in accordance with its own privacy notice. Based in the USA.</li>
          <li><strong>Google LLC</strong> &mdash; Search Console service for site-ownership verification and technical monitoring; processes data mainly in aggregated form. Based in the USA.</li>
          <li><strong>Consultants and professionals</strong> (e.g. the accountant) and <strong>competent authorities</strong>, where necessary to comply with legal obligations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Data is neither disseminated nor transferred to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>6. Transfers of data outside the EU</h2>
        <p>
          Some of the providers listed above are based or have infrastructure in the United States
          (Cloudflare, Meta, Google). Any transfers of data to third countries take place in
          compliance with Articles 44 et seq. GDPR, on the basis of:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>the <strong>EU-US Data Privacy Framework (DPF)</strong> adequacy decision: Cloudflare, Meta and Google are listed with an active EU-U.S. DPF certification on the official U.S. Department of Commerce list (<code>dataprivacyframework.gov</code>) as of the date of this notice;</li>
          <li>residually, <strong>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC)</strong> approved by the European Commission, together with adequate supplementary measures.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>7. Retention period</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact requests without a subsequent contractual relationship:</strong> data is retained for the time necessary to handle the request and in any case no longer than 24 months from the last exchange, save for any defensive needs.</li>
          <li><strong>Where a contractual relationship is established:</strong> for the entire duration of the relationship and, thereafter, for the period required by tax and civil-law obligations (generally 10 years, pursuant to Art. 2220 of the Italian Civil Code).</li>
          <li><strong>Browsing data and technical logs:</strong> for the technical periods set by the infrastructure providers.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>8. Data subject rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may exercise at any time the rights set out in Articles 15-22 GDPR: access to your
          data, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, portability, objection to
          processing, as well as withdrawal of consent where the processing is based on it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Requests should be addressed to <a href="mailto:info@brixiatech.com">info@brixiatech.com</a>
          or <a href="mailto:salfersrl@gigapec.it">salfersrl@gigapec.it</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority &mdash; the
          Italian <strong>Garante per la protezione dei dati personali</strong>
          (<a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.garanteprivacy.it</a>)
          &mdash; or, if you are located in the EEA, with your local supervisory authority, should
          you consider that the processing infringes applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>9. Nature of the provision of data</h2>
        <p>
          Providing your contact data is optional. Failure to provide it means the company will be
          unable to respond to your requests.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>10. Automated decision-making</h2>
        <p>
          The Controller does not carry out any automated decision-making, including profiling,
          within the meaning of Article 22 GDPR.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal__section">
        <h2>11. Changes to this notice</h2>
        <p>
          The Controller reserves the right to update this notice to reflect regulatory or
          organisational changes. The version in force is the one published on this page, with the
          date of last update indicated.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: clamp(120px, 16vh, 180px) var(--space-section-x) var(--space-section-y);
  }
  .legal__inner { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .legal__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    color: var(--c-pearl);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .legal__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    color: var(--c-mist-bright);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }
  .legal__lead {
    color: var(--c-mist);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 48px;
  }
  .legal__section { margin: 0 0 40px; }
  .legal__section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--c-pearl);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .legal__section p {
    color: var(--c-mist);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .legal__section ul {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    color: var(--c-mist);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal__section li { margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .legal__section a {
    color: var(--c-cyan);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 200ms var(--ease);
  }
  .legal__section a:hover { color: var(--c-pearl); }
  .legal__section a:focus-visible { outline: 1px solid var(--c-cyan); outline-offset: 3px; }
  .legal__section strong { color: var(--c-pearl); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal__section code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--c-copper);
  }
  .legal__row {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--c-copper);
    padding-left: 16px;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .legal__row-purpose {
    color: var(--c-pearl);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }
  .legal__row-basis {
    color: var(--c-mist);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .legal { padding: 110px 24px var(--space-section-y); }
  }
</style>
